{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d368af4f-c0d5-43b0-a3a2-8395aab79d94","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"865778b7-3a37-4b57-9bf6-ea4ec052296b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"6806:1FC0A0:162FE38:18FDF51:69FD3A65"},"id":"e0273243-8703-4c24-9149-abc7a724b048","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:20:44.345Z","parentId":"4a4d889a-221b-4370-b3ed-20cc4aa3b6b9"}
